  "intermediate_belief": "If I let people get close, they will eventually hurt or abandon me, so I must protect myself by keeping my guard up. If I am alone during important times, it means I am fundamentally flawed or unworthy of connection. I have to be vigilant because trusting others leads to disappointment.",
  "intermediate_belief_depression": "If I am spending the holidays alone, it proves that I will always be alone and nothing will ever change for me. No matter what I do, I can't escape this loneliness, so there's no point in trying.",
  "coping_strategies": "The client tends to withdraw and isolate to avoid potential conflict or emotional pain, especially during emotionally charged times like holidays. There is a pattern of ruminating on past relationship failures and perceived personal flaws, which intensifies feelings of sadness and loneliness. Aggressive or defensive behaviors may emerge when the client feels threatened or misunderstood, further straining relationships.",
